gurmukhi: ਲਾੲੀ ਰਾਜੇ ਸੰੁਭ ਨੋ; ਰਤੁ ਪੀਅੈ ਪਿਅਾਰੀ ||
transliteration: Laairaaje Sounbh No Rat(u) Peeai Pidaree||
translation: She struck it on the king Sumbh and this lovely weapon drinks blood.
Sumbh fell down from the saddle for which the following simile hath been thought.

gurmukhi: ਡੁਬ ਰਤੂ ਨਾਲਹੁ ਨਿਕਲੀ; ਬਰਛੀ ਦੁਧਾਰੀ ||
translation: That the double-edged dagger, smeared with blood, which hath come out (from the body of Sumbh);

gurmukhi: ਜਾਣ ਰਜਾਦੀ ੳੁਤਰੀ; ਪੈਨ੍ਹ ਸੂਹੀ ਸਾਰੀ ||੫੩||
translation: Seems like a princess coming down from her loft, wearing the red sari.53.

gurmukhi: ਦੁਰਗਾ ਅਤੈ ਦਾਨਵੀ; ਭੇੜ ਪੲਿਅਾ ਸਬਾਹੀ ||
translation: The war between Durga and the demons started early in the morning.

gurmukhi: ਸਸਤ੍ਰ ਪਜੂਤੇ ਦੁਰਗਸਾਹ; ਗਹ ਸਭਨੀ ਬਾਹੀ ||
transliteration: Sastra Pajeete Durgsaah Gad Sabhneen Baaheen||
translation: Durga held her weapons firmly in all her arms.

gurmukhi: ਸੰੁਭ ਨਿਸੰੁਭ ਸੰਘਾਰਿਅਾ; ਵਥ ਜੇਹੇ ਸਾਹੀ ||
transliteration: Sounbh Nisounbh Sanhaariaa Vath Jehe Saaheen||
translation: She killed both Sumbh and Nisumbh, who were the masters of all the materials.
Seeing this, the helpless forces of the demons, weep bitterly.

gurmukhi: ਮੋਹਿ ਕੁੜੂਚੇ ਘਾਹ ਦੇ; ਛਡ ਘੋੜੇ ਰਾਹੀ ||
transliteration: Muh(i) Kudooche Ghaah De Chhadd Ghode Raaheen||
translation: Accepting their defeat (by putting the straws of grass in their mouth), and leaving their horses in the way;

gurmukhi: ਭਜਦੇ ਹੋੲੇ ਮਾਰੀਅਨਿ; ਮੁੜ ਝਾਕਨ ਨਾਹੀ ||੫੪||
transliteration: Bhajde Hoe Mdareean Mud Jhaakan Naaheen||54||
translation: They are being killed, while fleeing, without looking back.54.

gurmukhi: ਸੰੁਭ ਨਿਸੰੁਭ ਪਠਾੲਿਅਾ; ਜਮ ਦੇ ਧਾਮ ਨੋ ||
transliteration: Sounbh Nisounbh Pathaaiaa Jam De Dhaam No||
translation: Sumbh and Nisumbh were dispatched to the abode of Yama;

gurmukhi: ੲਿੰਦ੍ਰ ਸੱਦ ਬੁਲਾੲਿਅਾ; ਰਾਜ ਅਭਖੇਖ ਨੋ ||
translation: And Indra was called for crowning him.
